location: The kidnapping took place in the village of La Vuelta in Buenos, Aires, Cauca, Colombia.
summary: 05/07/2011: On Saturday, in the village of La Vuelta in Buenos Aires, Cauca, Colombia, suspected militants from the 30th Front of the Revolutionary Armed Forces of Colombia (FARC) took hostage five civilians who were members of a local community counsel; identified as Jos Elder Viveros Delgado, Gueimar Alexis Viveros Delgado, Jos Eimer Viveros Delgado, Jaime Viveros Delgado, and Rmulo Viveros. The hostages were later killed on 05/11/2011. No group claimed responsibility for the attack.
target1: Five members of a local community council
motive: The specific motive for the attack is unknown.
weapdetail: Unknown weapons were used in the attack.
addnotes: The summary of this incident was partially based on an article originally written in Spanish.
